Ad Text:
Join RiskLogic and Help Build a More Resilient Tomorrow!

At RiskLogic, our vision is simple but powerful: to work with inspired people to build meaningful organisations that contribute to a better tomorrow. Every day, we empower our clients to navigate the most challenging situations with confidence. Through the right tools, training and experience, we help strengthen resilience maturity across organisations that shape our communities.

Who We Are

RiskLogic is a market‑leading consulting firm supporting corporate, not‑for‑profit and government clients across Australia.

Our culture is grounded in our values — Integrity, Passion, Innovation and Performance — and brought to life through our CREATE principles: Collaboration, Respect, Evolutionary, Accountable, Transparent and Enjoyable.

Our people come to work knowing they make a real, measurable difference in a constantly evolving threat environment.

About the Role

We are seeking a dynamic leader to support regional growth initiatives, drive performance, oversee high‑quality service delivery, and champion the wellbeing and development of our people. You will play a key role in upholding RiskLogic’s purpose, values and brand while ensuring exceptional outcomes for our clients.

Key Responsibilities

Operational

Manage and contribute to daily client deliverables across business continuity, crisis management, incident and emergency management.

Lead activities including program reviews, policy and framework development, BIAs, threat assessments, workshops, training design and facilitation, exercises, and technology configuration.

Build and maintain strong client relationships across diverse sectors.

Support local strategic alliances and partnerships.

Contribute to quality management and continuous improvement initiatives.

Collaborate across the Group to deliver integrated outcomes and identify cross‑sell opportunities.

Service clients across Australia, with interstate and occasional overseas travel.

Participate in negotiations, forecasting and managing client challenges.

Support performance management processes and other operational requirements.

People Leadership

Lead and support the performance of direct reports.

Help set and achieve key performance goals within the team.

Provide coaching, mentoring and ongoing feedback to support capability development.

Contribute to workforce planning and team growth initiatives.

What You Bring

Minimum 5 years’ experience delivering relevant services, ideally within consulting.

Expertise in at least one core RiskLogic service area.

Strong experience facilitating training sessions and exercises.

Proven ability to build trusted relationships at all levels.

Exceptional leadership, project management and organisational skills.

Strong problem‑solving capability and the ability to influence outcomes.

Commercial acumen and a performance‑driven mindset.

Ability to adapt to diverse environments and manage multiple priorities.

Excellent written and verbal communication skills.

A commitment to continuous improvement and quality delivery.

Self‑motivation and the ability to work effectively with remote teams.

A genuine desire for personal and team growth.




If you’re passionate about resilience, leadership and making a meaningful impact, we’d love to hear from you.

We will begin reviewing applications on 5 January 2026.

Job Description
Senior Data Engineer ( SQL / Azure Data Factory / Databricks )
Sydney / Hybrid
$140-170k base plus super
  
 
Senior Data Engineer (SQL / Azure / Databricks, Python) is required to join a growing Insurtech with a global presence.
This is an end-to-end role. You’ll own data products from source systems and Databricks
pipelines through analytics models, semantic layers, and Power BI dashboards

This is a great opportunity to join a growing company at an integral time - helping to establish their presence in Australia and having complete autonomy over technologies, projects and delivery.
  
Responsibilities:

Building and optimising data pipelines using Azure Databricks and ADF
Designing analytics-ready data models and semantic layers
Create and manage data engineering solutions, including data pipelines, data lakes, and transformation tools.
Generate insightful reports and dashboards for stakeholders.
Offer technical expertise and guidance to both team members and stakeholders.
Collaborate closely with stakeholders to identify business needs and translate them into effective technical solutions.
Stay current with emerging data technologies and provide recommendations to enhance existing systems.
Requirements:

Bachelor's or Master's degree in Computer Science, Information Systems, or a related field.
5-10 years of relevant experience.
Technical skills (SQL, Python/PySpark, Databricks, Power BI)
Proven expertise in building and developing data warehouses and ETL processes.
Experience with Databricks
Strong understanding of data architecture principles and practices.
Strong analytical skills to identify trends and patterns in complex datasets.
Excellent communication and interpersonal skills, enabling effective collaboration with clients and team members.
Preferred Qualifications:

Relevant certifications, such as Certified Data Management Professional (CDMP), Microsoft Certified: Azure Data Engineer Associate, or AWS Certified Big Data - Specialty.
Experience with cloud-based data solutions, including AWS, Azure, or Google Cloud Platform.
Knowledge of statistical modeling and machine learning.
Strong project management skills, with the ability to juggle multiple projects effectively.
Experience in the Insurance space would be a huge plus  
If you'd like to apply for the above Senior Data Engineer ( SQL / Azure Data Factory / Databricks ) role, please click apply now or send your resume to Olivia@talentisights.com.au
  
Keywords: Data Engineer / Analytics Engineer / Azure Data Factory / Databricks / Power BI / ETL / Data Science / Python /

At AustralianSuper, we truly care about our colleagues.​ We know work and life are intertwined. That's why we support the diverse needs of everyone and have policies that enable us all to thrive and be truly flexible. We ensure diversity is celebrated for the opportunity it provides us all to learn and grow and deliver better outcomes for members.

Your new role

This is a transformational leadership role designed to drive the next phase of maturity for Member data at the Fund. As Principal - Member Data Management, you will lead the team responsible for embedding data product management practices, delivering trusted and scalable data products, and enabling insight-driven decision-making across the Member domain.

Key duties include but are not limited to:

Actively drive adoption of emerging technologies such as AI and machine learning to automate data management & ops processes, enhance data quality, and unlock advanced techniques to enable business intelligence to provide a more seamless user experience and value.
Enable & roll out self-service data and analytics capabilities across the Member domain, ensuring trusted, well-governed data is easily accessible for decision-making and enabling business processes across various user personas.
As a member of the Data Services Leadership team, contribute to establishment of the function and development of its capabilities, and contribute towards uplifting the Fund's overall data capabilities and data risk posture
Proactively engage with colleagues at all levels, act as an evangelist for data management in the Fund, and communicate its significance in a crisp and meaningful manner
Collaborate and support the Head of Data Governance with the rollout of the data governance framework, key policies, and standards to the Member Domain.
Lead the development and ongoing maintenance of the data dictionary, business glossary, domains data models and lineage
Translate the 2035 strategy into clear priorities and actions for team, ensuring every team member understands how their work drives the Fund's purpose and long-term goals.
Culture - ensure the Fund's Members First culture is consistently and firmly embedded
Foster a high-performance culture by ensuring the team is empowered, accountable, and focused on delivering exceptional results through collaboration, continuous improvement, and innovation.

What you'll need

Proven track record of successfully delivering data & analytics transformation initiatives in a senior management capacity.
Embed agile principles and practices across the team, supporting iterative delivery, rapid feedback, and ongoing learning.
Mentor team members in agile methodologies, fostering a mindset of adaptability and continuous improvement.
Experience in developing and embedding data product management practices, deploying and managing critical data and insights products in a large, complex organisation.
Proven ability to embed data product management practices and oversee the lifecycle of data products to deliver measurable business value.
Experience enabling self-service data and analytics capabilities and driving adoption of data products across business domains.
Experience in enabling advanced analytics and AI teams.

Life at AustralianSuper

AustralianSuper is committed to colleague development, and we support our people with ongoing learning, coaching and training, as well as career opportunities across our expanding global organisation. We offer generous leave entitlements and promote a blended working environment in which all roles can flex, and we're happy to discuss what this looks like for you.

We are committed to supporting our diverse workforce in a way that is inclusive and embraces diversity in all its forms. If you require any reasonable adjustments to the recruitment process or the role, please let our recruitment team know.

What's next

Apply now, if you share our values of Energy, Integrity, Generosity of Spirit and Excellent Outcomes and would like the opportunity to work in a challenging, growing and rapidly evolving team to deliver outstanding results.

Australian or New Zealand citizenship or Australian permanent residency status is required.

Progress powered by purpose.

https://www.australiansuper.com/careers/candidate-privacy-notice

Agencies please note: this vacancy is being managed directly by AustralianSuper's Talent Acquisition team. We will contact our preferred agency partners should we require additional support. Thank you.

Squadron Energy is Australia's leading renewable energy company that develops, operates and owns renewable energy assets in Australia.

With proven experience and expertise across the project lifecycle, we work with local communities and our customers to lead the transition to Australia's clean energy future.

Why work with us?

Our goal is to improve the environment for current and future generations by leading Australia's transition to renewable energy. Our people are driven by their passion to make a meaningful difference in the world, to their families and friends, and to themselves.

Though we are united by this common goal, we view the tremendous diversity in our team's cultural, personal, and professional backgrounds as one of our greatest assets. This sense of camaraderie and cross-disciplinary expertise spurs drive and commitment to the growth of our business.

Squadron Energy is seeking a talented Energy Market Analyst to join our Gas Portfolio, Customer and Energy Markets team. Reporting to the Head of Gas Portfolio, you'll play a vital role in optimizing the performance and value of our natural gas and renewable energy portfolio-including the Port Kembla Energy Terminal, wind, solar, and storage assets.

Key Responsibilities
Analyse and monitor operational and financial performance of natural gas assets, supply, transport, storage, and customer arrangements
Prepare financial models, forecasts, and reports for projects and the overall portfolio
Undertake customer load analysis and support pricing structure development
Assist in developing new product offerings and refining asset strategies
Collaborate with cross-functional teams to assess market trends, technology, and regulatory changes
Update market forecasts and provide insights on market behaviour
Prepare and present technology review reports (e.g., long-duration energy storage)
Support completion of daily, monthly, quarterly, and annual reports
Interface with other business units for data and forecasts, including ESG, billing, and market risk information
General Responsibilities
Comply with all workplace health, safety, and environmental obligations
Ensure documentation is stored in the Squadron Energy document management system
Works independently with strong initiative, while demonstrating self-awareness and a willingness to seek guidance when faced with uncertainty
Escalate/report issues and risks to management promptly
Adhere to purchasing and expenditure procedures in line with approved budgets
Maintain professional relationships with all project stakeholders
Uphold Squadron Energy's employee policies and standards
Skills & Experience
3+ years' experience in the Australian Energy or Oil & Gas industry or relevant consulting sector
Sound knowledge of the energy industry, domestic gas market, LNG pricing, and the Australian Electricity Market (NEM)
Ability to create models for market and operational outcomes, including gas-powered generation and electricity market interactions
Experience with gas market and NEM systems
Strong analytical, problem-solving, and communication skills
Advanced Excel and database skills (SQL, APIs); Python experience or willingness to learn is highly regarded
Bachelor's degree in Engineering, Science, Economics, or Finance

Ready to make an impact in Australia's energy future?
Apply now to join Squadron Energy and help shape the transition to cleaner, smarter energy.





To Apply

Squadron Energy is committed to fostering a diverse and inclusive workplace. We welcome applicants from all backgrounds and strive to create an environment where everyone feels valued and respected.
Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people are encouraged to apply.

If you want to make a meaningful difference in this world then we encourage you to take the next steps:
* Submit your updated resume outling your relevant experience to date.
* Attach a cover letter outlining your motivations behind applying for this role.

Please Note

Appointment to this position will be subject to reference checks, a National Police Check and other applicable background screening if required.

Squadron Energy does not accept unsolicited CVs from recruitment agencies. Any unsolicited CVs received will not be considered, and no fees will be paid for such submissions.

Job Title: Sr. Business Analyst - SAP ERP Replacement
Ad Text:
SAP ERP Replacement Program - Senior Business Analyst


Project Overview The ERP Replacement Program will retire and decommission multiple financial applications across the organisation. Prior to decommissioning, all relevant data must be archived in line with the organisation's Data Retention Policy. Two validated archiving approaches are in scope:

Third-party commercial archive solution
Retain applications in read-only mode
The Business Analyst (BA) capability will drive requirements clarity to inform the final option(s), support the RFP (if Option 1 is selected), and ensure a compliant, user-friendly archive that meets reporting and retrieval needs post go-live (after 1 July 2026).
Applications in Scope
SAP ERP (primary), SAP Concur, Apliqo, OneSource Reporting, TM1, Xero
Great Plains, KwikTag, Fiscal Finance
Note: SAP ERP is the main driver for third-party solution selection. SAP Concur is proposed to be retained in read-only mode.
 
Current Status
High-level requirements: captured and socialized; scope updates pending (e.g., add Xero).
Detailed requirements: SAP ERP captured; not signed off.
Other apps: detailed requirements to be gathered (except SAP Concur read-only).
Role Details
Location: Melbourne, Victoria
Work Model: Hybrid (workshops with business & IT; vendor interactions)
Key Responsibilities (BA Capability)
Lead requirements planning for archiving across all in-scope applications; maintain traceability from policy to solution capabilities.
Own and iterate functional & non-functional requirements (including compliance, security, retention, retrieval SLAs, and audit trails).
Facilitate cross-functional workshops (Finance, Legal, Risk, Data Governance, IT Ops, Records Management, Business Units).
Prepare and present artefacts to Steering Committee and key stakeholders for decisions and progress checkpoints.
Interpret the Data Retention Policy and translate into implementable rules (e.g., retention periods, disposal schedules, data classifications).
Document current-state data flows and future-state archiving processes (ingest, index, query, report, export).
Finalize evaluation criteria to drive vendor selection, including data coverage, reporting, data extraction, multi-system capability, licensing model, and security.
Create RFP pack and support vendor Q&A, response scoring, demos/POCs, and recommendation to the Steering Committee.
Manage a Confluence/Jira repository of epics, user stories, and acceptance criteria; apply INVEST standards for story quality.
Coordinate with IT Ops/Support for run-book creation and operational handover (including read-only system monitoring).
Skills & Experience
Senior BA with 5+ years across ERP/Finance transformations and data archiving/decommissioning initiatives.
Strong policy-to-process translation skills (data retention, privacy, audit).
Experience with SAP ERP and at least two of: TM1, Xero, Great Plains, KwikTag, Apliqo, OneSource Reporting.
Proficiency in Jira/Confluence, process modelling tools (Visio/draw.io), and requirements traceability.
Demonstrated vendor evaluation/RFP experience, including solution assessment and POCs.
Excellent stakeholder management; ability to balance compliance, user experience, and cost across multiple systems.
Comfortable operating in hybrid environments and driving progress through structured artefacts and governance forums.

Silverstrand is seeking a Digital Solutions & Systems Lead to drive the development, adoption, and optimisation of technology across the company and become a key part in our strategic transition toward becoming a data-led civil construction business.

This newly created role plays a pivotal part in identifying business problems, developing practical digital solutions, and ensuring our systems, processes and data flows support efficient decision-making—from the field to the head office.

You will work closely with operational teams, project delivery, finance, HSEQ, and our existing MSP to understand needs, translate requirements, and implement scalable solutions that improve productivity, data quality, safety outcomes, and overall performance.

This is a hands-on, high-impact role suited to someone who thrives in environments where they can shape the future of technology in a growing business.

About the role:

Reporting to the Head of Finance.

Identify opportunities to digitise and streamline workflows across construction operations, plant, commercial, finance, HR, and safety.

Evaluate and implement practical IT tools, software, and systems aligned to business priorities and the Company’s long-term technology strategy.

Lead small-scale automation, integration and data-flow improvements (e.g., form digitisation, reporting automation, system linking).

Support the development of a unified data environment that enables accurate, timely insights from field operations to management.

Improve data capture processes (mobile apps, field tools, site reporting systems).

Ensure data integrity, consistency, and governance across systems.

Engage with project teams, supervisors, engineering, and commercial functions to understand real-world challenges.

Translate business problems into clear technical requirements and solution options.

Facilitate user testing, change management, and training to ensure smooth adoption.

Maintain and enhance key business systems (construction management, asset/plant, payroll interfaces, safety systems, document management, etc.).

Oversee vendor relationships and coordinate with our Managed Services Provider.

Develop scalable processes and documentation to support long-term system maturity.

Manage small to mid-size technology and process-improvement projects end-to-end.

Prepare business cases, cost-benefit analyses, pilot plans, and implementation roadmaps.

Ensure projects meet timelines, budgets, and business objectives.

Essential Skills and Experience:

Experience in a system support, digital solutions, business analysis, or IT process improvement role.

Strong understanding of operational workflows—ideally within construction, engineering, infrastructure, mining, transport, or similar industries.

Proven ability to analyse business needs and implement practical, fit-for-purpose solutions.

Experience with cloud applications, mobile tools, integrations, and data/reporting workflows.

Strong communication skills with the ability to work effectively with field and office-based teams.

Experience with construction management systems (e.g., Jobpac, Coins, Viewpoint, Procore).

Ability to manage multiple projects and priorities in a fast-paced environment.

Experience in data modelling or BI tools (Power BI, Tableau).

Understanding of API integrations, automation tools, or low/no-code platforms.

About Us:

Silverstrand is a privately owned company that provides high-quality civil engineering and construction services across Australia and New Zealand. Delivering projects that positively impact communities across the region, Silverstrand combines local knowledge with international expertise. Our projects include road, rail, airport, sewerage and water treatment, mining, renewables, and commercial industries.

To find out more about our company, head to our website - https://silverstrand.com.au/ 

If you are interested in the position please apply today!

Or contact: 

Joe Hedges - Resourcing Advisor

Email - J.hedges@silverstrand.com.au

About the opportunity

Lead internal project meetings and provide progress updates.

About you

A professional with 6+ years of consulting and implementation experience in HCM applications.
4+ years in a Consultant role working with HCM solutions.

If you're wanting to take the next step in your HCM Consulting career, we would love to hear from you!

Interviews will be commencing in January 2026

At Levande, we’re reimagining retirement living: creating vibrant, connected communities where people live well every day. Proudly Australian-owned and independent, Levande operates 59 villages nationally and continues to grow through a strong development and transformation pipeline.

We are seeking a Data Analyst to join our Finance team on a 6-month maximum term contract, based in Sydney. This role will play a critical part in ensuring accurate and reliable data within our ERP system, supporting pricing decisions and operational efficiency.

About the Role

Reporting to the Senior Change Manager, you will be responsible for sourcing, validating and maintaining unit configuration and square metre data within Levande’s ERP system. Your work will directly support pricing processes and data-driven decision-making across finance, pricing and sales teams.

This role is well suited to a detail-oriented data professional who enjoys working with complex datasets, improving data quality and collaborating with stakeholders.

Key Responsibilities

Source and validate unit configuration and square metre data from internal systems, architectural plans and supporting documentation
Analyse data quality, completeness and consistency, identifying discrepancies and anomalies
Apply data cleansing techniques to correct errors, remove duplicates and standardise formats
Prepare and manage uploads of cleansed data into the Levande ERP system
Monitor data integrity post-upload and troubleshoot issues as required
Collaborate with pricing, finance and sales stakeholders to clarify data definitions
Provide insights and reporting on data quality and readiness
Recommend improvements to data management processes, tools and automation initiatives

About You

Essential:

Proficiency in data analysis tools such as Excel, SQL and Power BI
Experience working with ERP systems (property or retirement living experience advantageous)
Strong understanding of data cleansing and validation techniques
Ability to interpret complex datasets and identify anomalies
High attention to detail and commitment to data accuracy
Clear communication skills and a collaborative working style

Desirable:

Familiarity with property unit measurements and pricing models
Exposure to retirement living or residential property operations

Why Join Levande?

Contribute to a purpose-led organisation with strong governance and growth
Work in a collaborative, values-driven environment
Sydney-based role with a defined 6-month maximum term contract

Next Steps

If your application progresses, you’ll be invited to complete a short, role-specific online video screening interview. This is designed to confirm alignment with the key technical and capability requirements of the role prior to progressing to an in-person interview.

Please note: this role is currently being progressed internally. We kindly request that recruitment agencies do not contact Levande regarding this vacancy.

If you’re ready to apply your data expertise in a values-led organisation and make an immediate impact, we’d love to hear from you.

Company Description


Supporting millions of Aussies since 1988 with low fees and competitive long-term performance. Profits back to members, not shareholders

Closing date: 2nd January 2026

Please note Rest does not accept speculative resumes from recruitment agencies 

Rest will review applications prior to the closing date and may close the role earlier 

Job Description


Established in 1988, Rest is one of Australia’s largest profit-to-member superannuation funds.

We support more than two million members, with around $100 billion of funds under management and are recognised as a responsible investment leader*. We believe when members understand and engage with their super, they’re more likely to get a better retirement outcome.

Everything we do at Rest is underpinned by our values and behaviours, we want to Be Daring, Keep it Simple, Take Action and Have Grit. To put it simply we want our people to thrive and love the work they do.

Rest’s Data, Technology and Delivery (DTD) business unit is accountable for planning and preparing the
organisation for the future through strategic technology innovation, as well as charting our business
strategy and executing for today and tomorrow.
Situated in the Business Analysis Practice, the Senior Business Analyst has two main priorities:
1. Supporting the Product Owner/Business Owner/Sponsors to ensure that business needs and
solutions options are understood
2. Ensuring the product/platform/project team have a shared understanding of the requirements,
through written and verbal communication.

We are looking for someone with a good blend of business and technical knowledge gained in a software development environment
- Strong data analysis expertise including data flows, data mining and data governance
- Experience working with HRIS platforms and clearing houses advantageous
- A good knowledge of the superstream standard and messaging framework

Qualifications


• Bachelor's degree
• IIBA® or similar industry standard certification preferred.
Required experience, understanding or credentials including:
• Business domain knowledge in superannuation or financial services desirable
• Ability to understand business functionality, business complexity and interdependencies
• Ability to develop compelling business cases with accurate cost and effort estimations
• Highly developed strategic, analytical, problem solving, issues management and evaluation skills to
deliver innovative solutions
• Understanding of modelling techniques, such as business process models and notation (BPMN), data
flow diagrams and unified modelling language (UML®), SIPOC and value stream analysis etc
Demonstrated experience in writing user stories and acceptance criteria

Additional Information


Our benefits have been designed so you can tailor your experience with us and include:

Personal and professional development opportunities 
Hybrid working 
Purchase leave scheme and gender neutral 16 weeks paid parental leave 
Super Contribution Continuation for 12 Months of parental leave 
Linkedin Learning 
Income Protection Insurance 
Rest Excellence awards (peer recognition awards based on Rest’s values and behaviours) 
Rest Stops - meeting free breaks 

If you share our values, believe you can help make a difference for our members and want to be part of a leading superannuation fund with a Super culture, please click Apply Now.

Rest is committed to creating a flexible work environment and culture that embraces diversity, equity, and inclusion - where people feel welcome, safe to be themselves and inspired to do their best.

We value the different backgrounds, lived experiences and abilities our diverse team brings. We welcome and encourage applications from candidates of all ages, cultural backgrounds, faiths, gender identities, sexual orientations and thinking styles. This includes people with disability, neurodiverse individuals, Aboriginal & Torres Strait Islander peoples and those with disrupted work history due to career or other breaks.

Please note only people with the right to work in Australia will be considered.

*Funds under management as at 31 July 2025. Rest is recognised as a Responsible Investment Leader by the Responsible Investment Association Australia (RIAA) in its Responsible Investment Benchmark Report 2022.

Category: Policy, Planning & Regulation, Government - State (Government & Defence)
Ad Text:
Lead Queensland's Government Statistician's Office in delivering high-quality statistical and demographic research services to inform public policy and decision-making across the Queensland Government.

• Provide expert advice to senior government stakeholders.
• Manage key relationships across agencies and jurisdictions.
• Lead a professional team to deliver strategic, impactful outcomes.

Your new opportunity
Be part of shaping Queensland's future! As the Government Statistician, you'll lead the Queensland Government Statistician's Office (QGSO) in delivering cutting-edge statistical and demographic services that inform critical public policy decisions and support government priorities.

This is a unique opportunity to drive evidence-based policymaking, manage high level relationships across government and other jurisdictions, and lead a team of skilled professionals. From population forecasting to crime statistics and land supply monitoring, your work will have a direct impact on Queensland's growth and success. Join us in fostering a culture of collaboration, leadership, and innovation.

In this role, you will:

Provide expert advice and analysis to senior government stakeholders to inform public policy and strategy.
Lead the delivery of statistical analysis, official surveys, and data management systems to support evidence-based decision-making.
Oversee and manage key relationships across government agencies, departments, and jurisdictions.
Ensure compliance with State and Commonwealth legislation to uphold data integrity and management standards.
Strategically lead and allocate resources to achieve departmental and government objectives.
